Sure, here are some example sentences that use the Serbian word "vrijedi" in different forms and positions, with the word highlighted with a star (*) and the English translations in parentheses:

1. *Vrijedi* li ova ponuda i dalje? (Is this offer still valid?)
2. Koliko *vrijedi* ova slika? (How much is this painting worth?)
3. Ona *vrijedi* za više od zlatnog dragulja. (She's worth more than a golden jewel.)
4. Ako nešto *vrijedi*, onda se moraš potruditi. (If something is worth it, then you have to make an effort.)
5. *Vrijedio* je svake sekunde koju sam proveo s njim. (He was worth every second I spent with him.)
6. Da li misliš da će ta ideja *vrijediti*? (Do you think that idea will be worth it?)
7. Koliko godina *vrijedi* taj automobil? (How many years is that car worth?)
8. *Vrijedilo* je čekati ovaj trenutak. (It was worth waiting for this moment.)
9. Oni *vrijede* mnogo više nego što mislimo. (They're worth much more than we think.)
10. Ne znam koliko *vrijede* ove informacije, ali ću ih podijeliti s tobom. (I don't know how valuable this information is, but I'll share it with you.)

I hope these examples help! Let me know if you have any other questions.